  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\n\r\nIn order to get through the [Getting Started docs](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/gh-pages/docs/_getting-started/index.md), the user needs to know about Consensus Clients and how to run them in tandem with Geth. \r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\n\r\nUsers going through the docs will run into the following error when running geth on goerli:\r\n```\r\nWARN [12-18|14:15:59.972] Post-merge network, but no beacon client seen. Please launch one to follow the chain! \r\n```\r\nTo get past this error, the docs should provide info on installing and running a consensus client.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\n\r\nNot yet, but I'm currently figuring it out.\r\n\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\n\r\nI'd like to help document this as soon as I can figure how best to do it.\r\n",
